article.description: — Darryl Morsell had a career-high 26 points as Marquette defeated New Hampshire 75-70 on Friday night.
article.headline: Morsell leads Marquette over New Hampshire 75-70
article.linkText: Morsell leads Marquette over New Hampshire 75-70
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- — Darryl Morsell had a career-high 26 points as Marquette defeated New Hampshire 75-70 on Friday night. Justin Lewis had 17 points and 11 rebounds for Marquette (2-0). Oso Ighodaro added 12 rebounds. Jayden Martinez had 21 points and eight rebounds for the Wildcats (1-1). Nick Guadarrama added 15 points and seven rebounds.
